               <interp inst="t18370814-2017" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/18370814"></interp>
               <interp inst="t18370814-2017" type="date" value="18370814"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18370814-2017-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-2017-18370814 t18370814-2017-offence-1 t18370814-2017-verdict-1"></join>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18370814-2017-charge-2" targOrder="Y" targets="def2-2017-18370814 t18370814-2017-offence-2 t18370814-2017-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>2017. <persName id="def1-2017-18370814" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-2017-18370814" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2017-18370814" type="age" value="15"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2017-18370814" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2017-18370814" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">SAMUEL SMITH</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted for<rs id="t18370814-2017-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18370814-2017-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18370814-2017-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> stealing, on the <rs id="t18370814-cd-214" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18370814-2017-offence-1 t18370814-cd-214"></join>12th of July</rs> 1 sugar-bason, value 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; and 1 pair of sugar-tongs, value 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; the goods of <persName id="t18370814-name-1408" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1408" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1408" type="surname" value="EVANS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1408" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18370814-2017-offence-1 t18370814-name-1408"></join>Thomas Evans</persName>: and 1 watch; value 15<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 1 chain, value 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; and 1 seal, value 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; the goods of <persName id="t18370814-name-1409" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1409" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1409" type="surname" value="THOMPSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1409" type="given" value="ADAM ALEXANDER"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18370814-2017-offence-1 t18370814-name-1409"></join>Adam Alexander Thompson</persName>: and </rs>
                  <persName id="def2-2017-18370814" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-2017-18370814" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-2017-18370814" type="age" value="22"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-2017-18370814" type="surname" value="BRIGHT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-2017-18370814" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">ROBERT BRIGHT</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18370814-2017-offence-2" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18370814-2017-offence-2" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18370814-2017-offence-2" type="offenceSubcategory" value="receiving"></interp> for feloniously receiving the same, well knowing them to have been stolen; against the Statute, &amp;c.—3rd <hi rend="smallCaps">COUNT</hi>, for receiving them of an evil disposed person.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370814-name-1411" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1411" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1411" type="surname" value="EVANS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1411" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS EVANS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Great Guildford-street, Southwark. On the 12th of July I went to my house and found a watch was gone from the mantel-piece—it belonged to Adam Alexander Thompson—I saw it safe about twenty minutes previous—I found I had lost a silver sugar-bason and tongs—they were my own—this is the bason and tongs and watch.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. JONES</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> How long had you seen these other things before? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I cannot say, because my partner took the bason out of the cupboard—I had seen them within a day or two—there is no mark whatever on them, but the balls have been marked with a pin—mine had two pin holes—the tongs are not found.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370814-name-1412" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1412" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1412" type="surname" value="SAUNDERS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1412" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES SAUNDERS</persName>
                  </hi>. I was standing opposite the prosecutor's about four o'clock, on the 12th of July, and I saw the prisoner Smith come out with a parcel in his hand in a red handkerchief—he had no shoes on—he met another lad, and the lad he met gave the prisoner his shoes, and took the parcel in the red handkerchief from him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Smith.</hi> If I waited to put on the shoes, why did he not come and catch hold of me?</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370814-name-1413" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1413" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1413" type="surname" value="BROOK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1413" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES BROOK</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable L</hi> 118.) I went on the night of the same day, and took Smith near St. George's Church, at twelve o'clock at night—I told him I wanted him for a felony—he made no reply—I took him to the station-house—he was locked up, and I and my brother officer went to Bright's house, and knocked at the door—he and his wife were in bed—I told him I wanted him on suspicion of receiving a watch, sugar-bason, and chain and seals—he said "You must be mistaken, as I know nothing about it"—we searched and found the sugar-bason in a hat-box.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Was there any one else in the house? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I believe there were two children—I found the hat-box in the front shop—there were several hat boxes piled up, but no hats in them—this was an open box without a lid—there were others piled on the top of it, and an old flannel petticoat put over the sugar-bason.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370814-name-1414" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1414" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1414" type="surname" value="GOFF"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1414" type="given" value="CHARLES BURGESS"></interp>CHARLES BURGESS GOFF</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable L</hi> 31.) I went to Bright's and found 113 duplicates, and among them was one for this watch, which led me to a pawnbroker, where I found the watch.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> You returned some? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, because I found they belonged to the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370814-name-1415" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1415" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1415" type="surname" value="ROWLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1415" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS ROWLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I was in the employ of Mr. Harris of the Minories,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183708140194"></xptr>
               <p>a pawnbroker—I have the watch which was pawned by Bright, on the evening of the 12th of July.</p>
               <p>(<hi rend="italic">Property produced and sworn to.</hi>) <hi rend="italic">Smith.</hi> I know nothing at all about them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">SMITH—
<rs id="t18370814-2017-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18370814-2017-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-2017-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 15—
<rs id="t18370814-2017-punishment-211" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18370814-2017-punishment-211" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18370814-2017-punishment-211" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-2017-18370814 t18370814-2017-punishment-211"></join>Confined Two Years; Two Months Solitary</rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">BRIGHT—
<rs id="t18370814-2017-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18370814-2017-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-2017-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 22—
<rs id="t18370814-2017-punishment-212" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18370814-2017-punishment-212" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="def2-2017-18370814 t18370814-2017-punishment-212"></join>Transported for Seven Years</rs>.</p>
            </div1>
